Re: He is cooking. He is being cooked.
by Mike Cash » Mon 06.01.2009 6:22 am NocturnalOcean wrote:It's an active sentence. Which means "Someone " is cooking him.If you want passive, you need passive.Unfortunately (for clarity) the passive voice can also be used in Japanese merely as a sort of politeness device, in which case the meaning is not passive at all.
