Re: He is cooking. He is being cooked.
by Okayamapiper » Sun 06.14.2009 9:22 pm 彼は料理をしています。He is cooking.彼を料理をしています。In this sentence, the subject is omitted but assumed to be the speaker and the sentence itself would not have any meaning pertaining to cooking as it would literally mean "I am cooking him". 料理can also mean to process, deal with, handle, treat....For example, 敵を料理する would be transled as "I defeated my opponent."ピッチャがバッターを料理した。The pitcher struck out the batter.For "He is being cooked" you would need the passive voice, requiring the される/られる　form.
Okayamapiper
Posts: 6Joined: Sun 06.14.2009 8:38 am
