Re: He is cooking. He is being cooked.
by Yudan Taiteki » Sun 06.14.2009 10:24 pm Okayamapiper wrote:彼を料理をしています。In this sentence, the subject is omitted but assumed to be the speaker and the sentence itself would not have any meaning pertaining to cooking as it would literally mean "I am cooking him". Just to reiterate, you cannot have two を in one clause; if the second one is dropped this is fine.
-Chris Kern
